---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const title = "Privacy Notice";
const description =
  "How wakirlabs.com handles personal data, under GDPR Art. 13 and § 25 TDDDG.";
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="essay">
    <header class="essay__header">
      <h1 class="essay__title">Privacy Notice</h1>
      <p class="essay__lead">
        How <code>wakirlabs.com</code> and the Wakir Labs newsletter
        handle personal data, under GDPR Art. 13 and § 25 TDDDG. The
        <a href="/de/datenschutz/">German version</a> is the legally
        binding text; this English page is a reading aid for
        international visitors.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="essay__body">
      <h2>Controller</h2>
      <p>
        Controller within the meaning of GDPR Art. 4 (7):
      </p>
      <p>
        [FIRMA]<br />
        [GESCHAEFTSADRESSE_STRASSE]<br />
        [PLZ_STADT]<br />
        Germany<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:hello@wakirlabs.com">hello@wakirlabs.com</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        Represented by: [GESCHAEFTSFUEHRER_KLARNAME]. Full provider
        information: <a href="/impressum/">Imprint</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Data we process when you visit this site</h2>

      <h3>Server logs (Cloudflare Pages hosting)</h3>
      <p>
        This site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. When you load a page,
        Cloudflare receives the following technical data, which is
        necessary to deliver the page to you:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Date and time of request</li>
        <li>Requested URL and HTTP status code</li>
        <li>User agent (browser and operating system)</li>
        <li>Referrer (if your browser sends one)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Legal basis: GDPR Art. 6 (1) (f) — legitimate interest in
        delivering and securing the website (defending against attacks,
        diagnostic logs).
      </p>
      <p>
        Cloudflare acts as a processor under GDPR Art. 28. The data
        processing agreement we have entered into with Cloudflare is
        archived in our compliance file
        (<a href="https://github.com/wakir-labs/site/blob/main/projects/legal/dpa-snapshots/MANIFEST.md" rel="external">
          dpa-snapshots/MANIFEST.md
        </a>;
        Cloudflare DPA reference:
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/cloudflare-customer-dpa/" rel="external">
          cloudflare.com/cloudflare-customer-dpa
        </a>).
      </p>

      <h3>Local storage (theme preference)</h3>
      <p>
        When you toggle between dark and light mode, your choice is
        stored in your browser's <code>sessionStorage</code> under the
        key <code>theme</code>. No data leaves your browser. Legal basis
        under § 25 (2) TDDDG: storage strictly necessary to provide the
        function explicitly requested by you (the theme toggle).
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not set advertising cookies. We do not load third-party
        analytics. There is no consent banner because there is nothing
        requiring consent.
      </p>

      <h2>Newsletter (Beehiiv)</h2>
      <p>
        If you subscribe to the Wakir Labs newsletter (<em>Field Notes</em>),
        we process the email address you submit and a confirmation
        timestamp.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Purpose:</strong> sending the newsletter you
          subscribed to.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legal basis:</strong> GDPR Art. 6 (1) (a) — your
          explicit consent, given via double opt-in.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Double opt-in:</strong> after submitting your
          address, you receive a confirmation email. Your subscription
          becomes active only when you confirm via the link.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Retention:</strong> until you unsubscribe. Every
          newsletter contains a one-click unsubscribe link.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Newsletter delivery is handled by beehiiv, Inc. (US, New York)
        as a processor under GDPR Art. 28. The data processing addendum
        we have entered into with Beehiiv is archived in our compliance
        file (<a href="https://github.com/wakir-labs/site/blob/main/projects/legal/dpa-snapshots/MANIFEST.md" rel="external">
          dpa-snapshots/MANIFEST.md
        </a>; Beehiiv DPA reference:
        <a href="https://www.beehiiv.com/dpa" rel="external">
          beehiiv.com/dpa
        </a>).
      </p>
      <p>
        Transfers to the United States are covered by the EU-U.S. Data
        Privacy Framework where applicable, and otherwise by Standard
        Contractual Clauses (SCCs) included in the Beehiiv DPA, Schedule
        A.
      </p>

      <h2>Processors at a glance</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Processor</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
            <th>Country</th>
            <th>Reference</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Cloudflare, Inc.</td>
            <td>Pages hosting, DNS, edge delivery</td>
            <td>USA</td>
            <td>
              <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/cloudflare-customer-dpa/" rel="external">
                DPA
              </a>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>beehiiv, Inc.</td>
            <td>Newsletter sending and subscriber management</td>
            <td>USA</td>
            <td>
              <a href="https://www.beehiiv.com/dpa" rel="external">
                DPA
              </a>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>
        The complete, time-stamped compliance file is at
        <a href="https://github.com/wakir-labs/site/blob/main/projects/legal/dpa-snapshots/MANIFEST.md" rel="external">
          projects/legal/dpa-snapshots/MANIFEST.md
        </a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights under GDPR</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Access</strong> your personal data (Art. 15)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Rectification</strong> of inaccurate data (Art. 16)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Erasure</strong> ("right to be forgotten", Art. 17)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Restriction</strong> of processing (Art. 18)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Data portability</strong> (Art. 20)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Object</strong> to processing based on legitimate
          interests (Art. 21)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Withdraw consent</strong> at any time, without
          affecting the lawfulness of prior processing (Art. 7 (3))
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, write to
        <a href="mailto:hello@wakirlabs.com">hello@wakirlabs.com</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory
        authority (Art. 77). The competent authority depends on the
        controller's seat
        ([AUFSICHTSBEHOERDE_NACH_GMBH_SITZ]).
      </p>

      <h2>No automated decision-making</h2>
      <p>
        We do not run automated individual decision-making, including
        profiling, within the meaning of GDPR Art. 22.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this notice</h2>
      <p>
        Material changes to this privacy notice are reflected in the
        site's commit history (<a href="/verify/">verifiable</a>). The
        currently published version is always the version in effect.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
</content>
</invoke>